The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for cell detection in microscopy images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method involves encoding the output pixel space using compressed sensing (cs.MM) and using a convolutional neural network (CNN) for regression (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of ensemble averaging, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
